31/01/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski continued his trip to Brussels on Tuesday (January 30th), meeting separately with EU security chief Javier Solana and European Commission (EC) President Jose Manuel Barroso. Both officials called for improved relations between the ruling majority and the opposition in Macedonia, for the sake of EU-related reforms. Barroso says the EC would set a date for starting accession talks in its next regular report, due by the end of the year. 
Also Tuesday, the third session of the Macedonia-EU Joint Parliamentary Committee wrapped up. In a joint statement, the EU representatives expressed certainty that Macedonia has the capacity to accelerate reforms. They also announced that the EU plans to ease visa rules for Macedonia this year. (Vecer - 31/01/07; MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 30/01/07)
